VIM Cursor Movements
h â€“ move cursor left
j â€“ move cursor down
k â€“ move cursor up
l â€“ move cursor right
H â€“ move to top of screen
M â€“ move to middle of screen
L â€“ move to bottom of screen
w â€“ jump forwards to the start of a word
W â€“ jump forwards to the start of a word (words can contain punctuation)
e â€“ jump forwards to the end of a word
E â€“ jump forwards to the end of a word (words can contain punctuation)
b â€“ jump backwards to the start of a word
B â€“ jump backwards to the start of a word (words can contain punctuation)
0 â€“ jump to the start of the line
^ â€“ jump to the first non-blank character of the line
$ â€“ jump to the end of the line
g_ â€“ jump to the last non-blank character of the line
gg â€“ go to the first line of the document
G â€“ go to the last line of the document
5G â€“ go to line 5
fx â€“ jump to next occurrence of character x
tx â€“ jump to before next occurrence of character x
} â€“ jump to next paragraph (or function/block, when editing code)
{ â€“ jump to previous paragraph (or function/block, when editing code)
zz â€“ center cursor on screen
Ctrl + b â€“ move back one full screen
Ctrl + f â€“ move forward one full screen
Ctrl + d â€“ move forward 1/2 a screen
Ctrl + u â€“ move back 1/2 a screen
