VIM Text Manipulation
i â€“ insert before the cursor
I â€“ insert at the beginning of the line
a â€“ insert (append) after the cursor
A â€“ insert (append) at the end of the line
o â€“ append (open) a new line below the current line
O â€“ append (open) a new line above the current line
ea â€“ insert (append) at the end of the word
Esc â€“ exit insert mode
r â€“ replace a single character
J â€“ join line below to the current line
cc â€“ change (replace) entire line
cw â€“ change (replace) to the end of the word
c$ â€“ change (replace) to the end of the line
s â€“ delete character and substitute text
S â€“ delete line and substitute text (same as cc)
xp â€“ transpose two letters (delete and paste)
u â€“ undo
Ctrl + r â€“ redo
. â€“ repeat last command
